<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910219-0062</DOCNO><DOCID>910219-0062.</DOCID><HL>   BankAmerica to Shift   A Savings-Bank Unit   To Commercial Banks</HL><DATE>02/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7C</SO><CO>   BAC</CO><IN>MAJOR MONEY CENTER BANKS (BAN)BANKS (BNK)SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS, CREDIT UNIONS (SAL)</IN><LP>   SAN FRANCISCO -- BankAmerica Corp. said it will convert asavings-bank unit, Federal Savings Bank, into severalcommercial-bank units.   BankAmerica last September announced its plan torestructure the unit after it acquired Benj. Franklin FederalSavings andamp; Loan Association from the Resolution Trust Corp.and began operating it as Federal Savings Bank. FederalSavings, with headquarters in Portland, Ore., has 88 branchesin four states.</LP><TEXT>   BankAmerica said it will convert the unit's business intoseparate state-chartered commercial banking operations. TheOregon branches will become part of BankAmerica's SeafirstBank Oregon unit, which will be renamed Bank of AmericaOregon. The Idaho branches will be operated as Bank ofAmerica Idaho, the Washington operations will merge intoBankAmerica's Seafirst Bank unit and the Utah branch will betransferred to Bank of America Arizona, BankAmerica said.</TEXT></DOC>